message.content: cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.HC. The paper discusses the integration of search functionality within mobile platforms and the use of chatbots and conversational systems, which are topics related to natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of AI and machine learning techniques, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category as well. Additionally, the paper discusses the user experience and human-computer interaction (HCI) aspects of chatbots and mobile search, which makes cs.LG (Learning) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) possible sub-categories.
